omWeb?topicID=27401.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://tuvedeq.homestead.com/Files/ND.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: healing</span><hr size=1> I'm worried that they'd think they needed to nerf our nuking if they increased our heals. Honestly at this point, I don't want any caster balancing. I really think they will just break the game further. <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=194540">Magelo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ul1nd4r4.showPublicProfile?language=EN>L1nd4r4</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/02 12:34:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27401.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: healing</span><hr size=1> &quot;I can see having a new spell that healed 2k for 600mana with a 7second cast time.&quot;<br>
 <br>
  Doubtful unless Clerics get a DL upgrade.  DL is 2.7 hp/mana instant heal, NT is 2.2 hp/mana instant heal.  2k for 600 is 3.3 hp/mana.  What makes druids such crappy healers is a) lack of CH's massive 10 or 20 to 1 or better healing, b) lack of high efficiency low agro but not instant heals (celestial elixir and Torpor.)  For b, yes we have Nature's Recovery but 30hp/tick is frankly a complete joke when typical mobs are hitting for 400 in Ssra, 300 in CT, ST, ToV, and 200 to 300 in most tougher xp zones The Deep etc.  Haveing to wait THREE MINUTES for a 900hp heal is just not comparable to what Torpor or CE gives you.  If you consider Nature's Recovery decent then start a necro because they'll far outheal you. <br>
 <br>
  I doubt we'll get low agro pulse heals, we're supposed to cast a NT and have every uncontrolled mob in the area eat our leather clad butts alive, and thats stepping on the cleric's toes like giving clerics fire nukes would be for us.  I doubt we'll get a higher efficiency instant heal than clerics without clerics getting a CH upgrade or a DL upgrade, but it's possible.  And even with a 3.3 hp/mana heal we're still, again, far and away, outclassed by shaman's 6 to 1 torpor (not to 75% slow which is just obscenely broken and overpowered, and their over 100mana/tick regen) and cleric's 5ish to 1 CE and 10 or 20 to 1 CH.<br>
 <br>
  Short of a 1k for 200 mana heal, which frankly ain't going to happen despite cleric nuke upgrades letting them outnuke us at certain levels and come respectably close at 60, we just aren't going to be healers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/02 12:36:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27401.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: healing</span><hr size=1> Caster balancing has to consider high-end balancing because that is where the greatest imbalance is.  It is really only in the 50+ area that the caster imbalance becomes more and more apparent, and it becomes glaringly obvious in the high end raid.<br>
<br>
In other words, if Verant attempts "caster balancing" without considering the high-end situation, then it won't really achieve any balancing at all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utalyenatrueheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talyena Trueheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/02 12:41:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27401.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: healing</span><hr size=1> Actually, I think druids are pretty well balanced all the way up to 60. It is only when you get into high end raiding that druids are messed up. I think they should bump natures touch down to 58 or so and then add some improved healing at 60. Or just modify nature's touch to be a better heal than it is. I also am all for removing the stupid healing penalty over 50 or completely.<br>
<br>
I'm not worried about the nukes so much. I actually believe they will be buffing up overall nuking power when they do caster balancing and the worst thing that could happen to us is we get left where we are and are passed by mages. That wouldn't bother me because I think that either way we will end up with nuking power very close to what mages end up with and I don't see them getting nerfed. <p><font size="+1"><i><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="-1"><b>Talyena Trueheart (Dawntreaders)<br>
  Hierophant of Tunare<br>
  Terris-Thule</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/02 12:51:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27401.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: healing</span><hr size=1> We aren't ever going to get CH, and CH will pretty much always dwarf anything else.  What we need, and what wouldn't require a large decrease in our power in some other area (like nuking), would be:<br>
<br>
1. Removal of 10% penalty (would apply to all classes) on heals.<br>
<br>
2. Addition of a reasonable Group Heal (when compared to clerics and paladins).<br>
<br>
The latter would be of help on raids with AoE damage mobs, and would enhance our support healing role.  <br>
<br>
Beyond this base line, any druids wishing to be better at healing can choose the appropriate AA skills and alteration specialization. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugupwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gupwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/02 1:15:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27401.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: healing</span><hr size=1> It's been a while since I've read or posted to this board, mostly because even at lvl 53, the prospects for my druid have become limited and I've been finding my rogue more enjoyable.  That being said, I'm going to make a statement that I'm almost sure is going to bring flames, and I'm positive has been discussed elsewhere, but I'm gonna be lazy and not go find it.  Verant is talking about &quot;balance&quot; in casters.  I have 2 words in response to this, as the issue does more than unbalance casters, but unbalances the game as a whole.<br>
<br>
Nerf<br>
Manaburn<br>
<br>
Verant has made the statement that after a given amount of time, certain encounters should become trivial, but some things are just stupid.  I point to one issue in particular, just because it sticks out for me.  On my server, 5 manaburn wizards and a bard (yes, that's ONE group) killed Gorenaire with 0 deaths.  If anyone here can show me any other class that can accomplish this given the same levels and AA abilities, I'll retract my statement.  I don't care if it's 5 druids, or 5 warriors and a bard, or whatever...  put 5 of any class together with a bard and kill Gore with no outside assistance to show me that wizards aren't overpowered.  It can't be done.  Now, perhaps VI will find a way to make Gore a trivial encounter for a group of lvl 59+ people regardless of class, but I really don't see it happening.  VI likes to talk a big game about balancing, but I don't see them actually pulling it off. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useriena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seriena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/02 1:24:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27401.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: healing</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Nerf<br>
Manaburn<br>
....<br>
put 5 of any class together with a bard and kill Gore with no outside assistance to show me that wizards aren't overpowered. It can't be done. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
/agreed<br>
<br>
But on a different note, a cold debuff would be nice. Or toss cold, fire, atk, ac debuff all in one, make it the druid version of Malo. (oh boy I can hear the cries of overpower on that idea).  But wait, there's more. Don't make it so that it hardly ever lands or that we have to debuff in order to debuff (i.e. Ro's Smoldering Disjunction). Make it actually useful and needed on high end encounters.<br>
<br>
So, in summary:<br>
<br>
1. Nerf Manaburn<br>
2. Improve our healing (a better ratio Nature's Touch and Nature's Recovery = Topor)<br>
3. Give us a debuff like Malo but for cold/fire/atk/ac<br>
4. Fix our epic<br>
<br>
Do these things and I'll be happy. <p><br><br><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117440" TARGET="_NEW">Seriena,</A> 60 druid<br>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=185839" TARGET="_NEW">Joolz,</A> 57 Monk<br>
<A HREF=http://www.soldiers-of-light.net/>Soldiers of Light</A></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useriena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seriena</A> at: 5/23/02 11:39:52 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaccretion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Accretion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/02 1:39:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27401.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What about this...</span><hr size=1> Not to be too simplistic, but what about giving upper lvl Druids a massive DoT?  I believe the top Druid DoT is Winged Death (1287) at lvl 53 or so.  Why not give like a 2000-2200 DoT (similar to the Shaman) which would stack with other races and allow simultaneous nuking/DoTting, thus substantially increasing Druid DPS output?  I know this idea has been discussed at length, but it seems to me that the most powerful arguments for Druid balance lie in their poor damage output, NOT the healing weaknesses.<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utettsuo1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tettsuo1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/02 1:55:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27401.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~harulestokes/_uimages/StupendousManCharacter.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What about this...</span><hr size=1> I'll give ya 2 reasons not to give Druids such a large DoT upgrade.<br>
<br>
1.  Shaman has the DoTs Druids have to nukes.  Giving Druids a large DoT, leaves Shaman behind on the damage front.<br>
<br>
2.  Shaman and Necros would throw a FIT!<br>
<br>
I personally think Druids should get either a Torpor like heal (low mana heal with side-effects), or an upgrade to Nature's Recovery (50hp per tick single target only with an instant recast time for a total of 1200hp healed). <p>
57 Grasshopper of the Celestial Fist<br>
48 Bard of Jazz Fury<br>
41 Druid of Furry Feet<br>
Druzzil Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ul1nd4r4.showPublicProfile?language=EN>L1nd4r4</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/02 2:04:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27401.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What about this...</span><hr size=1> &quot;2. Addition of a reasonable Group Heal (when compared to clerics and paladins).&quot;<br>
 <br>
  Again this steps on cleric's toes.  Part of being a better healer is being flexible.  But changing Nature's Recovery to be a group spell would be nice.  As it is it's nice but not as efficient as short duration heals and a horrible pain to time and it comes nowhere close to the necro theft line 720 in 9 ticks ZONEWIDE range to everyone in the party, or their 600 mana for 300 mana to everyone in the party (including the necro.)<br>
 <br>
  Any case where you're using Nature's Recovery as your primary heal Necros seriously outheal you.  And while their lack of NT makes them less than ideal healers for most raids for groups their mez can often compensate.<br>
 <br>
  Although there isn't anything wrong with getting outhealed by necros whose domain is life and death any more than us outnuking them when our domain is nature and the elements.  I would like more rock crushing and lightning bolting in my nukes though.  =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upoitez.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poitez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/02 2:18:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27401.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: healing</span><hr size=1> Druids are relatively balanced until they get to raiding at 60.  I'm sure by now I've easily spent as much time, and more than likely much more, being 60 as 1-59.  At 60 a druid falls well below the curve in healing, in particular, and some other categories as well.  I would suggest giving druids a group Elixir series and/or a radically changed buff/debuff line.  Honestly I believe we need a major updrade; something as powerful as slow/CH, something that gives us a purpose.  I'll submit, for your approval, a quick comparison between druids and clerics.<br>
<br>
In kind of an argument/counter argument fashion I'll try to match up cleric skills vs. druid skills to strengthen my point.<br>
<br>
I figure Druids' porting and Clerics' ressing is relatively equal (some may disagree).  Both are massive timesavers, high end raiding as we know it would not exist with out both.<br>
<br>
Healing- Obviously Clerics well out match druids in healing.  Even discounting CH clerical healing is more efficent, quicker casting, and available in group + elixir varieties.<br>
<br>
Nuking- Druids have a decent edge in nuking with the advent of Moonfire.  I don't think it's anywhere near enough of a seperation though (in relation to the difference in healing).  I'd say we nuke about 15% better or so; of course we have no good magic based nukes and that's all clerics get; so it's hard to compare.  I think the exact ratios are 2.85/1 and 3.29/1 (or about 13% difference).<br>
<br>
Damage Shields-  I hate even talking about damage shields because ours aren't the best and thus not even really used in high end raiding, especially with a creator dagger.  Clerics of course have Mark of Karn/Retribution.  I'd honestly trade my DS's for the clerical ones, but that's my opinion.  There are drawbacks; they can be resisted etc...  They are however unique and useful in raiding.<br>
<br>
Buffing (other than DS) - Umm, no comparison; not even close.<br>
<br>
I'll clump other utility stuff together.  Clerics and druids get root, Druid root is much better.  We both get stuns (sorta) Clerics' stun is much better.  Druids have dots; they're semi-useful; but mobs have limited debuff slots and stacking DoD and other crap that could take the place of a good necro DoT isn't worth it.  I'd include snare in this discussion if I knew of a single high end encounter that it really adds anything to.<br>
<br>
So basically it doesn't look too bad from there.  We might be a bit underpowered but nothing horrible; unless of course clerics get the single most game breaking spell.  Which they do...  That's what we really need.  A whole new thing (whether heal, nuke, debuff, buff or otherwise) that makes people have a need for druids on raids.  <br>
<br>
Also, going off the Manaburn tangent, we could use some kind of cool AA skill too.<br>
<br>
-Venerable Poitez<br>
-Bertox<br>
<br>
*edit* As I was thinking about it...  I think a good upgrade for us would be a line of let's call them &quot;infusion&quot; spells.  Spells that would be relatively short duration buffs that would infuse a target with some power of nature.  They'd have to have a longish recast but be relatively powerful.  Could be things like a 2 minute buff (with 3 min recast or so) that would make the target be healed for 1/4 the damage he deals or something.  Or one that infuses a caster with focus item-esque effects (IE a few minute 30% additional damage on nukes).  Could give the person an extra damage proc with +/- aggro. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upoitez.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poitez</A> at: 5/23/02 11:29:02 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugrolmn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grolmn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/02 2:39:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27401.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: healing</span><hr size=1> Druids, Shamen, and Clerics should be given a level 58 2k heal.  The Cleric heal should be more efficient.<br>
<br>
Druids should be given a AoE HoT.  Like 800hp over 4 ticks to all group members in an area of effect.<br>
<br>
As far as nuking goes, I think we are fine.  We can do quick damage if necessary, but our long term DPS isn't that great.  That is a price we pay for versatility.<br>
<br>
Finally, I still think Druids should get an upgrade to Winged Death.  Level 53 for our last DOT for a class that uses DOTs so much through their career just doesn't seem right. <p>Peppin Bramblefist<BR>
Heirophant of Tarew Marr<BR>
